volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Registration/Check-in","individual_id":"019b7ac9-920b-70bb-8a36-b4b700fb52d4","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Ardis Dull","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Registration/Check-in","individual_id":"019b7adf-f250-735f-9fc9-46fd3e9119b1","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Marjorie Stratton","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Registration/Check-in","individual_id":"019d0e9a-060a-7334-a060-a824b8eb02ea","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Rebeccah Stratton","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Start","individual_id":"019d0a40-c419-799a-97ec-c9f1967b2d4c","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Bob Stratton","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Start","individual_id":"019b7ac9-920b-7530-b85a-103e52302ff8","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Will Enger","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null}],"organizing_club_id":"01912f3e-e3e1-7e8e-b3c6-32387a8b4990","result_source_brief":"CascadeOC Website: https://www.cascadeoc.org/result/wednesday-evening-series-4-forest-park/","organizing_club_name":"Cascade Orienteering Club","cumulative_event_comments":"Unfortunately, control #11 on Course 3 (code 125) was misplaced and several people were unable to find it. That leg has been voided from the course and results have been adjusted accordingly. RouteGadget still has the original course and splits.\n\nThe fourth event in the 2018 Wednesday Evening Series will be held at Forest Park, in Everett. The Wednesday Evening Series is our most relaxed, casual set of navigation events, held in local parks once the weather warms up. These events are a little more low-key than those in the WIOL/Winter Series, and we always offer a barbecue afterward for all participants. Decompress after work, with or without your coworkers. Or meet your family at the park and enjoy a night off from cooking. Or meet a bunch of friends at the park for an evening of exploring together, chatting over some food, and finishing up with frisbee on the lawn.\nEvents in the Wednesday Evening Series are generally less challenging (both physically and navigationally) than many of our other events, and are therefore great for beginners and those less experienced with orienteering – while also offering a challenge to longtime participants of the sport.\nForest Park, while small in acres, is an intriguing combination of several types of terrain (shaded city park, white forest, green forest, and open campus) with a variety of elevation changes thrown in for fun. We’ve got a full range of courses where we’ve achieved some distance and route choice with almost no course overlaps – primarily just for safety when crossing a busy road. The map has had some recent updates, so you should be able to navigate off of vegetation reasonably well."}
